{"id":464902,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_shirts","text":"=\"preserve\">Redshirts or Red coats is the name given to the volunteers who followed Giuseppe Garibaldi. He was an Italian revolutionary who unified Italy by conquering the Kingdom of the Two Sicilies in 1861.\nThe name came from the color of their shirts.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Volunteer","surface_form":"volunteer","offset":60},{"uri":"Giuseppe_Garibaldi","surface_form":"Giuseppe Garibaldi","offset":84},{"uri":"Italy","surface_form":"Italian","offset":114},{"uri":"Revolutionary","surface_form":"revolutionary","offset":122},{"uri":"Unification_of_Italy","surface_form":"unified","offset":140},{"uri":"Invasion","surface_form":"conquering","offset":157},{"uri":"Kingdom_of_the_Two_Sicilies","surface_form":"Kingdom of the Two Sicilies","offset":172},{"uri":"Shirt","surface_form":"shirt","offset":247}]}